      <div class="msgContentFrame">With several helpful threads floating around I figured why not create a good source of information that answers all those nasty FAQ for Gladiators. <br /><pre> 
<u><b>Table of Contents</b></u> 
I. Starting Out 
 A. Stat Point Allocation 
 B. Becoming a Gladiator. 
 C. Why is shield so important? 
 D. Early Leveling 
II. Gladiator Abilities. 
III. Other Abilities. 
IV. Tanking 101 
 
<u><b>Gladiator 101</b></u> 
<b>I. Starting Out.</b> 
A. Stat Point Allocation 
   STR - Physical Attack Damage. 
   VIT - Physical Attack Defense, Max HP. 
   DEX - Physical Attack Accuracy, Evasion, Physical Critical Rate. 
   MND - Magical Attack Defense, Cure Potency, Max MP. 
   PIE - Magical Attack Accuracy. 
   INT - Magical Attack Damage. 
 
   My stat layout is 15%STR, 50% VIT, 35%DEX. 
   50% VIT - More HP! This is huge, you need to be able to tank damaging weapon skills and spells. 
   35% DEX - Evasion! Accuracy/CritRate seems to add more damage than STR at early levels. 
   15% STR - Still not to be ignored. Take this to 40 after getting Ample VIT and DEX. 
 
B. Becoming a Gladiator. 
  1) Obtain a Weathered Gladius from one of these <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/item.html?ffxivitem=4030010#Sold_By" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/item.html?ffxivitem=4030010#Sold_By">NPCs</a>. 
  2) Obtain a Shield from this <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/mob.html?ffxivmob=1600054" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/mob.html?ffxivmob=1600054">NPC</a> or from a Bazaar. Not required but extremely important:Read Below 
  3) ??? 
  4) Profit. 
 
C. Why is a shield so important? 
  Gladiators are able to gain two skills while fighting.  
    Sword: Your main Gladiator rank. 
    Shield: Something called Sentinel. 
  Sentinel has a chance to raise every time you block(which is a Full Block or Partial Block). 
  At Rank10 Sentinel you gain a skill called Aegis Boon. Guards turn damage into heals! 
  Sentinel is difficult to raise this is why you want a shield early in your Gladiator Career. 
  Partial blocks occur VERY often when the Guard skill is up. 
  Guards lead to significantly reduced damage. 
  You CANNOT block spells or TP abilities used by enemies. 
 
D. Early Leveling 
  Use Guard often to begin earning Shield rank. 
  Levequests are a great way to earn quick experience and gil. Do yours than offer to help others. 
  Be aware of Red Lotus Blade's mana cost. 
  If you are using a Gladius Light Slash will be more effective. Daggers should use light stab. 
  Once you reach rank 8 start learning to use Phalanx. 
  My advice: Relax during fights. Don't spam your skills. Wait and try to get 1 action per press. 
    This allows Phalanx to be used easier. Its easier to learn this in solo play than in a busy party. 
    Server lag makes it very very frustrating at times so practice staying calm. 
    Your parties will thank you. 
 
E. Your Role in a Party. 
  Gladiators make excellent tanks. You should use provoke to pull any stray mobs off of your mages. 
  Keep everyone alive. Because of the way AoE heals work in FFXIV. Allowing a PUG or MAR to offtank 
  for a few seconds is desirable. 
  Try to build aggro by blocking and then using Phalanx. 
  Provoke @10 gives you a few seconds of guaranteed aggro. It does not give much enmity though. 
   
   
    
 
<b>II. Gladiator Abilities.</b> 
  + Positive Note   
  ♫ Neutral Note 
  - Negative Note 
 
<a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/abilitylist.html?name=&amp;rank_low=&amp;rank_high=&amp;class=3&amp;equip=1&amp;order_by=" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/abilitylist.html?name=&amp;rank_low=&amp;rank_high=&amp;class=3&amp;equip=1&amp;order_by="><u>Sword Abilities</u></a>: 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=22103" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=22103">Light Slash</a> - Our first basic attack 
    ♫ Slashing damage. 
    + Does more damage than Light Stab 
    - Less Accurate 
    - Higher stamina cost 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26822" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26822">Light Stab</a> - Our second basic attack 
    ♫ Piercing damage. 
    + More accurate than Light Slash. 
    + Lower stamina cost 
    - Lower damage output 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26713" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26713">Red Lotus</a>(r2): 1000TP, 10MP :: Our first TP required Skill 
    + Has a VERY high accuracy bonus. 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26680" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26680">Rampart</a>(r4) - Our second damage mitigation. Drastically reduces damage taken. 
    - 5 Minute cooldown 
    - This more of a reactionary skill when you are in over your head and need an extra boost. 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26794" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26794">Circle Slash</a>(r6): 1000TP :: Our second TP skill. AoE physical damage. 
    + Unlike Red Lotus this requires no MP. 
    ♫ AoE can hit non-aggroed targets so watch yourself! 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26797" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26797">Phalanx</a>(r8): 250TP :: A reaction based Weapon Skill. Can only be used after a block. 
    + Very low TP cost 
    + Very High Damage 
    + Very low Stamina cost(0 Stamina!) 
    - Must be used after a block which can be difficult with server lag 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26685" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26685">Provoke</a>(r10): Forces enemy to attack you. 
    - High stamina cost. 
    - 20 second cooldown. 
    - Wears off the monster quickly 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26800" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26800">Spinstroke</a>(r12): 1000TP :: Deals slashing damage. Increases attack power when enemy is not engaging you. 
    + Great way to get aggro back after losing it. Can do upwards of 300 damage @ rank 12. 
    - No damage bonus when enemy is facing you. Still a great TP dump. 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26689" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26689">Still Precision(r14)</a>: Increase accuracy and reduce evasion. 
    + 45s duration 
    + Evasion loss may induce more blocks for more phalanx strikes. 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26806" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26806">Howling Vortex</a>(r16): Deals slashing damage and temporarily increases enemy's casting times. 
    + Great damage and no mana cost 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26692" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26692">Obsess</a>(r18): Increase defense against a single target while lowering it to others. 
    + Can claim a monster without generating hate(meaning it turns red but won't attack) 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26804" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26804">Onion Cut</a>(r20): TP1000 :: Deals slashing damage. Not Recommended! 
    - Damage equivalent to Howling Vortex 
    - Horrible accuracy rating 
    - Large stamina cost(almost 50%) 
    - Large cooldown(45s) 
    + Reportedly can burst out exceptional damage but it is unknown how to trigger 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26858" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26858">Heavy Slash</a>(r20): Deals slashing damage and increases Enmity. 
 
<a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/abilitylist.html?name=&amp;rank_low=&amp;rank_high=&amp;class=10&amp;equip=1&amp;order_by=" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/abilitylist.html?name=&amp;rank_low=&amp;rank_high=&amp;class=10&amp;equip=1&amp;order_by="><u>Shield Abilities</u></a>: 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=22111" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=22111">Guard(r1)</a>: Our bread and butter skill for damage mitigation. 
    ♫ Equipped automatically when you put a shield in your OffHand. 
    ♫ To get this to the desired action slot(lets say 2) first equip RedLotus to slot 2 
      then equip it over Guard and they will swap positions. 
    ♫ 15s duration 
    + Using this increases your Block rate siginificantly. Recommendeded to keep Guard up at all times. 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27760" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27760">Aegis Boon(r10)</a>: Increases defense against frontal attacks and converts blocked damage into HP. 
    ♫ 1 Minute cooldown 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27953" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27953">Shield Bash(r14)</a>:Deals blunt damage. May interrupt casts and render the target unable to cast again for  several seconds. 
    + Great for interrupting skills such as Imp's Incantation ability 
 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27944" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27944">Outmaneuver(r20)</a>:Increases defense against frontal attacks and increases TP generated by blocks. 
 
<u>Gladiator Guild Abilities</u>:The required Rank(second number) must be met AND they must be purchased with     Gladiator's Guild Marks 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26858" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26858">Heavy Slash(r20/r??)</a>, 6000 Marks: Deals slashing damage increasing enmity. 
    + Does more damage than light slash. 
    - Requires more stamina. 
    - Extra enmity generated is not outstanding. 
  <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=29469" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=29469">Self Preservation(r30/r22)</a>, 8000 Marks: Increases guard length by 50% 
    + This raises your guard length by 7s at r30. 
    + At r22 this increases guard length by 4s(~25% increase in length). 
    + Great for those who are lazy but also conserves stamina. 
 
<b>III. Other Useful Abilities.</b> 
Another post by myself. 
<a href="http://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1285373635152578419&amp;page=1" title="http://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1285373635152578419&amp;page=1" rel="external">http://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1285373635152578419&amp;page=1</a> 
 
<b>IV. Tanking 101</b> 
Great Post by Aurelis. 
<a href="http://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1284601906299455930&amp;page=1" title="http://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1284601906299455930&amp;page=1" rel="external">http://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1284601906299455930&amp;page=1</a> 
</pre> <br /> <br />Still a work in progress. Any feedback(+ or -) is appreciated. As well as any suggestions for new sections or information I have overlooked or missed. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 24th 2010  6:01pm by Brentmeister </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 24th 2010  6:02pm by Brentmeister </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 24th 2010  6:02pm by Brentmeister </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 24th 2010  6:03pm by Brentmeister </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 24th 2010  6:05pm by Brentmeister </span></i></div>
