      <div class="msgContentFrame"><b>F.A.Q</b> <br /> <br /><b>Should I use equipment above my Rank?</b> <br />Unfortunately the best answer I can give is &quot;it depends&quot;. <br />Equipping gear with a higher rank requirement will cut into its effectiveness. However, at a certain point the higher rank gear may become more effective. The best thing to do is equip your current weapon, then equip the weapon you are thinking of swapping to and note the stat changes. If it doesn't give any benefit you may need to wait a rank or two to equip it. Also remember higher rank gear is more expensive to repair! As a general rule of thumb I try to stay away from equipment that is more than 5 ranks above me. <br /> <br /><b>How should I open up tanking a mob?</b> <br />Light Stab -&gt; Provoke -&gt; Guard -&gt; (Still Precision) -&gt; Phallanx <br />Light Stab is our most accurate TP generating skill so opening with it generates the TP needed to use Phalanx. <br />To keep hate just try to DPS as much as you can and use provoke sparingly. Keep that shield up for extra TP! <br />Still Precision is an optional but recommended. <br /> <br /><b>Why shouldn't I open with provoke?</b> <br />A mob does not have an enmity table loaded until it is red. <br />Using provoke on a yellow monster will NOT generate any enmity effectively wasting the stamina and cooldown. <br /> <br /><b>How do I use Aegis Boon?</b> <br />1) Acquire Rank 10 Sentinel. <br />2) Navigate to Shield class under Actions &amp; Abilities. <br />3) Click on Aegis Boon. <br />4) Click &quot;Equip to offhand&quot;. <br />5) Now go restore HP for blocking! <br />If the skill is gray you probably messed up step four. If you are sure you didn't re-login and it will fix. <br /> <br /><b>What is the Gladiator's Guild and how do I earn Guild Marks?</b> <br />The Gladiators Guild gives special Gladiator-only quests. The first of these can be undertaken by going to the guild at rank 20 and talking to the NPC behind the counter. Successfully completed Gladiator Quests give guild marks and gil. <br />The Gladiators Guild offers many purchasable actions and traits to those with enough guild marks. You must purchase these abilities AND reach the required rank to use them. <br />Guild Marks can be earned by Gladiator Quests(R20+), R20+ Leves(R13+) and Faction leves. It may take many days to acquire enough marks to purchase an ability. <br /> <br /><b>What is Class Affinity and how does it affect me?</b> <br />Class Affinity limits the effectiveness of abilities carried over from another class. For Example: The skill Second Wind will restore 200+HP on Pugilist and only restore 150+HP on Gladiator. <br />Factors: <br /> ~ Current Class <br /> ~ Current Rank(You cannot use a R20 ability from Gladiator on a R1 Conjurer effectively. <br /> ~ Others to be discoverd! <br /> <br /><b>What useful abilities can Gladiator offer my class?</b> <br />I encourage you to visit your class forum for more information but here are a few that I carry over regularly. <br />Provoke - Useful for Pug,Mar,etc who want/need to tank <br />Still Precision - +ACC useful for disciples of war <br />Red Lotus - VERY VERY accurate weaponskill. Great for skillups on an class <br /> <br /><b>Why do I level slower thank my friends in parties?</b> <br />Each battle grants a maximum of 500 skill points. Gladiators must split this 500 between sword and shield skill. If you get 200 shield skill in a fight you can only get 300 sword skill. The solution is to not use your shield but I can't really recommend letting your sentinel level fall so far behind. If you are not hitting the maximum 500 then this is a non-issue and you are leveling slower because you are missing too often. I recommend using stab/red lotus is this is the case. <br /> <br /> <br /><b>Skill Bars:</b> <br />Almost always the same: <br />1. Light Stab(if I miss) / Light Slash (if I am not missing) <br />2. Cure <br />3. ******* <br />4. Guard <br />5. Phalanx <br />6. Red Lotus Blade <br />7. ******* <br />8. Second Wind (Pug-r6) <br />9. ******* <br />0. Punishing Barbs (Thau-r10) <br />11. Rampart (r8) <br /> <br /><u>Leve Party:</u> <br />3. Provoke (r10) <br />7. Ferocity (Lanc-r4) <br />9. Shock Spikes(Conj-r4) / Taunt (Pug-r10) / Aegis Boon (Sent-r10) <br /> <br /><u>Grinding Party:</u> <br />3. Obsess (r20) <br />7. Howling Vortex (r16) <br />9. Still Precision (r12) <br /> <br /><u>Solo Leveling:</u> <br />3. Obsess (r20) <br />6. Howling Vortex (r16) <br />7. Aegis Boon (Sent-r10) <br />9. Shock Spikes (Conj-r6) <br />0. Radiance (Conj-r10) <br /> <br /><b>Useful Links:</b> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.ventusinvictus.blogspot.com/" rel="external nofollow" title="www.ventusinvictus.blogspot.com/">ventusinvictus.blogspot.com</a> <br />A great blog maintained by an experienced Gladiator's narration on what he learns in his travels. Great info. He reaches many of the same conclusions I do but not all. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 18th 2010  4:45pm by Brentmeister </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 24th 2010  9:27pm by Brentmeister </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 26th 2010  4:11am by Brentmeister </span></i></div>
