      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">grazypanda wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />But is this guide for group players or also solo players (i think grouping)? Because for a gladiator in a group is tanking most important. But if you solo then i would suggest putting more points in STR and less in DEX. You have skills like Still Precision that increase accuracy.</div></div> <br /> <br />This is actually a common misconception. As a whole STR isn't that great of a stat at lower levels for gladiator. Imagine this. <br />These are ESTIMATES for LOWER LEVELS(&lt;20)and likely wrong numbers but the idea is right <br />10 Points of STR = +10% per attack <br />10 Points of DEX = 10% more dodges, 10% More attacks Landed, 10% more crits <br /> <br />Now lets say you do 50 damage per hit and the mob has 500HP. <br />+10% dmg will add 50 damage to this fight. <br />+10% Accuraccy will add 50 damage to this fight. <br /> <br />The DEX ends up giving you the same/more damage increase while also helping you maintain a better HP pool. At higher levels STR may become more important as the stats get larger but early levels all my experience points to DEX winning out. It worked this way in FFXI too for the most part. <br /></div>
