      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Dartagon wrote:</div><div class="orig">Since this seems to be a pretty good thread I have 2 questions in regards to GLA. <br /> <br />First: On shield the wield rate stat (i think). Anyone know what this stat does? <br /></div></div> <br /> <br />Current belief is that it is the stat that reflects how often you will block with a shield. AFAIK there has been not testing on this. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Dartagon wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />Secondly: Does anyone know the actual penatly for using weapons armor above your rank? <br /> <br />IE: Is it better to use rank 9 at rank 13 then using Rank 27? <br />Any testing being done on this? <br /></div></div> <br />The answer to this questions is the dreaded... <br /> <br />IT DEPENDS! <br />More testing needs to be done and we need more data to know what weapon/armor is most effective at what level. However, it is known that using an item that exceeds your rank will not give the full benefit of that item. The best way to know this is to put on a piece of gear. Check your stats. Then put on another and check your stats. Eventually the item with the higher rank will give better stats so you just have to check it each level.</div>
